{{Politics of Bolivia}}
'''Referendums on departmental autonomy statutes''' were held in four [[departments of Bolivia]]—[[Beni Department|Beni]], [[Pando Department|Pando]], [[Santa Cruz Department (Bolivia)|Santa Cruz]], and [[Tarija Department|Tarija]]—in May and June 2008. These four departments, known as the ''[[Media Luna]]'', voted in favor of autonomy in the June 2006 elections. The National Electoral Court had blocked the referendums, along with the proposed [[Bolivian constitutional referendum, 2008|referendum on Morales's new constitution]]. The referendums were also unconstitutional, as the constitution in force at the time had no provisions for departmental autonomy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boliviainfoforum.org.uk/documents/535424538_BIF%20Bulletin%20Special%20edition%20May%202008.pdf |title=Bolivia Information Forum Bulletin, May 2008 |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=2010-12-26}}</ref> Under the Framework Law on Autonomy, passed in 2010, the autonomy statutes must be harmonized with the 2009 Constitution before being enacted. [[Image:Bolivia media luna.png|thumb|left|Departments of Bolivia]]
The first [[Santa Cruz autonomy referendum, 2008|autonomy referendum]] was held in [[Santa Cruz Department (Bolivia)|Santa Cruz Department]] on 4 May 2008. Autonomy referendums were held in [[Beni Department]] and [[Pando Department]] in [[Bolivia]] on 1 June 2008<ref>[http://edition.cnn.com/2008/WORLD/americas/06/01/bolivia.vote.ap/index.html?eref=rss_world Bolivian states vote on autonomy - CNN.com]{{dead link|date=December 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/7429630.stm |title=Bolivian regions 'back autonomy' |publisher=BBC News |date=2008-06-02 |accessdate=2010-12-26}}</ref> Both departments approved autonomy with slightly over 80% of the vote.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web |author=AFP |url=http://afp.google.com/article/ALeqM5iuy48CI1ocml0QdNgrzCIgX5jZ_w |title=Defying Morales, two Bolivian provinces back autonomy |publisher=Afp.google.com |date=2008-06-01 |accessdate=2010-12-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110520140211/http://afp.google.com/article/ALeqM5iuy48CI1ocml0QdNgrzCIgX5jZ_w |archive-date=2011-05-20 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> Turnout was only 34.5% in Beni and slightly over 50% in Pando.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kommentar posten |url=http://derstandard.at/?url=/?id=3357344 |title=Siege für Autonomieanhänger |publisher=derStandard.at |date= |accessdate=2010-12-26}}</ref>
A [[Tarija autonomy referendum, 2008|similar referendum]] was held in [[Tarija Department]] on 22 June 2008.<ref name=autogenerated1 />
