{{for|the Canadian community formerly known as Eskimo Point|Arviat}}

'''Eskimo Point''' ({{coord|74|17|S|162|33|E|}}) is a flat-topped, steep-sided promontory which protrudes from the east side of [[Eisenhower Range]] and forms the north wall of [[O'Kane Canyon]], in [[Victoria Land]]. 

So named by the [[Southern Party]] of [[New Zealand Geological Survey Antarctic Expedition]] (NZGSAE), 1962-63, which camped on its upper surface and built an igloo while waiting for white-out conditions to lift.

