[[File:Severo-Muyskiy.jpg|thumb|right|The Severomuysky Range, seen from a train on the [[Baikal Amur Mainline]].]]
The '''Severomuysky Range''' ({{lang-ru|Се́веро-Му́йский хребе́т|translit=Severo-Muyskiy khrebet|translation=Northern Muya Range}}) is a mountain range in [[Buryatia]], [[Russia]], part of the [[Stanovoy Highlands]]. It separates the basins of the [[Upper Angara River|Upper Angara]] and [[Muya River]]s.
The [[Baikal Amur Mainline]] (BAM) railway traverses the southern end of the mountain range via the [[Severomuysky Tunnel]].
