{{Infobox company |name = Specim, Spectral Imaging Ltd Oy |logo = [[File:Specim_company_logo_2015.jpg|170px|Specim logo]] |type = Limited company, [[Osakeyhtiö]] |foundation = June 7, 1995 <ref name="Kauppalehti Specim 2018" /> |location_city = [[Oulu]], Finland <ref name="Kauppalehti Specim 2018" /> |area_served = Worldwide |key_people = Risto Kalske [[Chairman]], Tapio Kallonen [[Managing director]] <ref name="Kauppalehti Specim 2018">, [http://www.kauppalehti.fi/yritykset/yritys/specim,+spectral+imaging+oy+ltd/10079234 Kauppalehti company registry].</ref> |products = Imaging spectrograps, spectral cameras and systems |industry = [[Hyperspectral imaging]] <ref name="Kauppalehti Specim 2018" /> |num_employees = 58 (2017) |homepage = http://www.specim.com }}
'''Specim, Spectral Imaging Ltd''' is a European technology firm headquartered in [[Oulu]], Finland. Specim manufactures and sells imaging spectrographs, [[hyperspectral]] cameras and systems. Specim's airborne AISA [[hyperspectral imaging|hyperspectral cameras]] have been utilized for example in monitoring the environmental effects of major industrial catastrophes such as [[Deepwater Horizon oil spill]] and [[Red mud spill]].<ref name="Kaleva Specim 2010">[http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/oulusta-lahtee-mittalaitteita-ympari-maailmaa/877968 Kaleva: Oulusta lähtee mittalaitteita ympäri maailmaa].</ref><ref name="Mikkola 2010">Mikkola, A, (Nov 16, 2010), Kaleva, Näkyvästä näkyvää.</ref>
In 2010, Specim was widely credited for its Thermal Infrared Hyperspectral Cameras, including a position as a Prism Awards finalist.<ref name="Prism Awards 2010">The Prism Awards for Photonics. [http://www.photonicsprismaward.com/finalists.aspx The 2010 Finalists]</ref> The credited Specim Owl is world's first Thermal Hyperspectral Camera that can efficiently be used for outdoor surveillance and [[UAV]] applications without an external light source such as the Sun or the Moon.<ref name="Frost&Sullivan Specim Owl">Frost&Sullivan, Technical Insights, Aerospace&Defence (Feb 2011): [http://www.frost.com/prod/servlet/segment-toc.pag?segid=D870-00-48-00-00&ctxixpLink=FcmCtx3&ctxixpLabel=FcmCtx4 World First Thermal Hyperspectral Camera for Unmanned Aerial Vehicles].</ref>
In 2013, together with Germany’s Forschungszentrum Jülich research centre, Specim developed and thoroughly tested the novel Hyplant airborne hyperspectral sensor. This was the first airborne sensor to map the fluorescence over large areas. Since then it has been used to map various types of vegetation all over Europe and also in the USA. This project is one step in assessing feasibility of possible new [[ESA]] satellite instrument that could provide global maps of vegetation fluorescence called the Fluorescence Explorer (FLEX).<ref name="ESA (2014)"> ESA (2014): [http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Observing_the_Earth/The_Living_Planet_Programme/Earth_Explorers/Future_missions/Glowing_plants_a_sign_of_health Glowing plants a sign of health]</ref> <ref name="ESA 2015"> ESA (2015): [http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Observing_the_Earth/The_Living_Planet_Programme/Earth_Explorers/Plant_power_from_above Plant power from above]</ref>
